parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine cooling system failures can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage, stalling, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: smoke entering the interior of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mechanical failures can cause the engine to stall, seize, or fail, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Exhaust system failures can cause fires, damage to surrounding components, and decreased vehicle performance.
Head gasket failures can cause engine damage, overheating, and decreased vehicle performance.

The failure of the strut mount can cause the strut to break loose from its mounting, potentially leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle's body and surrounding components.
symptoms: The strut breaks loose from its mounting
the strut bursts through the trunk or other body panels
unusual noises or vibrations while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat latch or track can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: allowing the seatback to come forward toward the windshield when brakes are applied
the front seats do not lock in position
the driver's bucket seat breaks and comes off track while driving.
